<$transclude $tiddler="$:/plugins/rimir/doc-template/templates/page">
<$fill $name="body">

!! What it does

Turn any tiddler into a //dashboard//: a free-form canvas onto which you drop other tiddlers as freely arrangeable tiles. Each tile transcludes a target tiddler; you move it, resize it, restyle it, and click it to open the underlying tiddler in the story river.

Tag a tiddler with <<tag "$:/tags/rimir/dashboard">> and a view-template body cascade entry swaps its body for the dashboard canvas — no special editor, no separate app.

!! Key features

* ''Drop to add'' — drag any tiddler from the wiki onto the canvas and it becomes a tile. Or type a title and press //Add tile//.
* ''Batch-add by filter'' — type any filter above the canvas and press //Add matching// to add a tile for each tiddler it selects, laid out in a grid.
* ''Clean'' — remove all tiles (or only those whose target matches a filter) in one confirmed step.
* ''Free-form layout'' — absolute pixel positioning; drag a tile to move, drag its bottom-right corner to resize. Geometry is saved on release.
* ''Bring-to-front z-order'' — interacting with a tile raises it above the others; the stacking order persists.
* ''Two tile styles'' — a //window// tile with a title bar and controls, or a //bare// tile that is just the resizable content.
* ''Actions menu'' — each tile's actions live behind a ⋮ menu in the corner, revealed on hover or keyboard focus: ↗ open-external (when available), ⧉ show-in-popup, ⊟ toggle window/bare, × remove.
* ''Choose what a tile shows'' — the body by default; uploaded images/PDFs show their thumbnail, and a tiddler with no text but an `icon` shows its icon. Override per tile (⋮ menu: auto / body / icon / any field), or per dashboard with filter-based //display rules//.
* ''Group (meta) tiles'' — a group tile is itself a free-form canvas you can drop other tiles into; groups nest recursively. Collapse/expand with ▸/▾, rename inline, and drag tiles (or whole groups) between containers to re-home them.
* ''Click to open'' — a click (as opposed to a drag) opens the tile's target tiddler in the story river; ''Ctrl/Cmd-click'' opens the target's external link (`url` / `_canonical_uri`, fields configurable) in a new browser tab.
* ''Ctrl-drag to duplicate'' — hold Ctrl/Cmd while starting a drag to drop a copy of the tile elsewhere (the same tiddler may appear on any number of tiles).
* ''Show contents in a popup'' — the ⧉ control opens the target in a centered popup rendered through the default ViewTemplate (title, tags, fields and body), without leaving the dashboard.
* ''Kind-aware'' — when a tile's target is a [[rimir/kind|$:/plugins/rimir/kind]] instance, the window tile shows the type's icon (with the type name as hover text) before the caption. Silently absent when kind is not installed.
* ''Plain-field storage'' — every tile is its own system tiddler with ordinary editable fields (`x`, `y`, `w`, `h`, `z`, `target`, `style`). No JSON blobs.

!! Quick start

# Click ''New dashboard'' in the page controls (right sidebar → Tools), or tag any tiddler <<tag "$:/tags/rimir/dashboard">>.
# Drag a few tiddlers onto the canvas.
# Move, resize, and restyle them; click one to open it.

See the ''Examples'' tab for concrete recipes and ''Reference'' for the full field and tag list.

